SalesCopenhagen20.07.2020 

 Our new colleague will be responsible for Heimdal Security sales in Scandinavia, with a focus on the Danish marked. This person will work together with our current sales team to handle partner management and actively pursue new sales opportunities in the region. 

 Ideal Candidate 

 The person we seek is ambitious, driven and focused; 

 Excellent Interpersonal skills; 

 Ability to speak with conviction; 

 A natural in picking up the phone and calling; 

 No industry knowledge required, we can teach you what you need; 

 Be a firm believer in the math of sales, knowing success is a combination of hard work, strong priorities and high quality; 

 Have chosen to never become complacent in life, but aim to develop yourself and people around you every day; 

 Know that working as a team and supporting a strong feedback culture will get us all where we want to go – faster. 

 What we offer 

 An attractive salary package with a high bonus package; 

 Extremely challenging projects; 

 A fast-growing company outlook and huge personal growth potential; 

 A competitive, dynamic & awesome team; 

 A fun, flexible and relaxed work environment; 

 A central office location in Copenhagen. 

 Responsibilities 

 Our new colleague will be responsible for Heimdal Security sales in Scandinavia, with a focus on the Danish marked. This person will work together with our current sales team to handle partner management and actively pursue new sales opportunities in the region. 

 Requirements 

 Previous sales experience with Cold Calling customers; 

 Winner mentality; 

 Very strong skills in using a computer and the Office package; 

 Danish and English fluent language capability (Swedish/Norwegian language is a plus); 

 The job will entail up to 30 travel days per year. 

 Full time1 position available 
About us 

 At Heimdal Security we protect users and companies from cyber-criminalactions, by keeping critical information and intellectual property safe. We're one of the fastest growing companies in the cyber security industry, being focused on user education through our blog and free online courses and resources. 

 We are the winners of the "Most Educational Security Blog" award in 2016, nominated for Anti-Ransomware Solution of the Year at the 2017 Computing Security Awards and Winners of the “Anti Malware Solution of the Year” at the 2018 Computing Security Awards. 

 Since 2011, we have been leading the fight against cybercrime, developing new technologies and providing intelligence to protect over 6,000 companies and 900,000 users against cybercriminal attacks and data security breaches.

